To find out how many cereal bits were in each design, we can divide the total number of cereal bits by the number of designs. 

63 cereal bits / 9 designs = 7 cereal bits per design (approximately)

It's important to note that this is an average and not necessarily the exact number of cereal bits in each design. Since Emily created these designs herself, it's possible that she didn't use an equal number of cereal bits in each one. She might have used more or fewer cereal bits depending on the complexity of the design. However, based on the given information, we can estimate that there were approximately 7 cereal bits per design on average.
